# Next.js Rules

## Routing

- Use the App Router (`src/app`) exclusively; avoid the Pages Router.
- Co-locate route handlers under `route.ts` or `route.tsx`.

## Components

- Default to React Server Components (RSC).
- If a component needs browser-only APIs, add `"use client"` at the top.

## Data Fetching

- Use `fetch`, `getServerSideProps`, or `server actions` inside server components.
- Cache responses with `revalidate` or `ISR` when appropriate.

## Performance

- Wrap client components in `<Suspense>` with fast fallbacks.
- Use the `next/image` component with `loading="lazy"` and WebP formats.

